Anyone looking to solve Nvidia Driver Altered error. The check is comparing your Nvidia driver version to what is defined in the allowed constants.
https://github.com/Datura-ai/compute-subnet/blob/main/neurons/validators/src/services/const.py

For example, my executors all broke when the driver 550 apt package updated from 550.142 to 550.144.03 because 550.144.03 is not defined in this list of constants. To solve this you could explicitly install a supported driver version by downloading the package from NVIDIA or just stay on top of installing apt packages that have a support driver version and not allowing the driver to update.

sudo apt-get install nvidia-driver-570-server gives you a supported driver version right now.
